{
  "texts": [
    "The main properties of the GWB signal observed in DR2new and examined in this paper are shown in Fig. 1.",
    "The length of the dataset is T = 10.3 years, and excess common correlated power is detected in several frequency bins up to ≈30 nHz (Fig. 1 left panel).",
    "Conversely, some bins are unconstrained, which results in a relatively loose determination of the spectral properties of the observed signal.",
    "In the literature, h c and S in Eqs.",
    "(1) and (3) are usually anchored to the pivotal frequency f 0 = 1 yr -1."
  ]
}